## Core Component Breakdown

### 1. The Dynamic Network Matrix

The `aws_subnet.Dynamic_subnet` resource uses the variable loop to carve out distinct blocks:
`cidr_block = "10.0.${count.index}.0/24"`
When `ec2_count` is evaluated at its default value (`3`), this automatically generates three distinct segments: `10.0.0.0/24`, `10.0.1.0/24`, and `10.0.2.0/24`.

### 2. Upstream Image Discovery (Data Source)

Instead of relying on hard-coded AMI IDs (which break across different AWS regions or become outdated over time), the `data "aws_ami"` block queries the live AWS marketplace. It filters specifically for official Canonical HVM SSD builds of `Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS (Jammy Jellyfish)`, grabbing the latest version dynamically before deployment.

### 3. Even Compute Distribution

To prevent instances from clustering inside a single network boundary, the compute layer uses indexed mapping:
`subnet_id = aws_subnet.Dynamic_subnet[count.index].id`
This binds `aws_instance.ex1[0]` to `Dynamic_subnet[0]`, `aws_instance.ex1[1]` to `Dynamic_subnet[1]`, and so on.

